div.p:
The Secretary’s comments on the situation in the various countries were briefly
                    stated as follows: 

Pakistan, strongly anti-Communist;

Ceylon, one of the most anti-Communist countries in the area;
                            officials insistent that the United States not desert Chiang Kai-shek;

Indonesia, situation complicated by variety of political parties but
                            believed government would be formed excluding Communists;

Thailand, categorical assurances given by officials that Thailand
                            would not go Communist, also definitely not neutral;

Vietnam, situation miraculously better than a year ago;

The Philippines, situation continues good.
